<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929437>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 25. Cardiodactylus guttulus (Matsumura, 1913): variation observed in male genitalia along geographical distribution. (A) specimen from Southern Vietnam (angular dorsal ridges in lateral views); (B) specimen from Northern Vietnam (very similar to specimens from Japan and Taiwan). From left to right, male genitalia in lateral, ventral and dorsal views." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4929437/files/figure.png" .

